#   CODE-008: beagle: one sub-spawn helper; fold relay dup

beagle's submodule plumbing is heavily pasted: four fork+chdir(<wt>/<sub>)+execvp+reap bodies (BERecurseInto, be_index_mount_dog, be_recurse_capture, bepost_spawn_sub), with bepost_spawn_sub a functional duplicate of BERelaySub. The FILEReap→BEDOG translation and the read-stdout-to-EOF loop are also pasted. Factor one spawn helper and reuse BERelaySub.

##  Issues

Four fork+exec+reap bodies, a dead-dup relay, and pasted reap/read loops.

 -  Four fork+chdir+execvp+reap: SUBS.c:109,200,272 + bepost_spawn_sub (BE.cli.c:2078).
 -  bepost_spawn_sub ≈ BERelaySub (SUBS.c:371) = be_recurse_capture + --tlv + HUNKu8sRelay; reinlined argv-pack.
 -  FILEReap→BEDOG* translation open-coded at BE.cli.c:114,142, SUBS.c:179.
 -  read-stdout-to-EOF loop pasted SUBS.c:338,425, BE.cli.c:2180.

##  Blockers

None, but spawn/recurse is load-bearing — keep the suite green and gate the diff.

##  Planned

One BESpawnSub + one reap-translate + one read-to-EOF; route all callers.

 -  Repro first (§17): recursive get/post/put over a submodule fixture stays green.
 -  Collapse the 4 spawns to BESpawnSub(wt,sub,argv); bepost_spawn_sub → BERelaySub.
 -  FILEReapToBEDOG() + BEDrainToEOF() helpers replace the pasted blocks.

